ce:section.ce:para:
Fig. 4
a shows the Raman spectrum of the as-prepared GQDs. Raman spectrum of the GQDs shows a disordered (D) band at ∼1350cm−1 and a crystalline (G) band at ∼1600cm−1. The intensity ratio of the D to G band (ID/IG
) was 0.74, which is smaller than previously reported values for GQDs produced by exfoliation of GNPs in organic solvents using a vortex mixer. [17] This result indicates that the as-prepared GQDs have a large portion of sp2 carbons with fewer defects. In addition, as the Raman laser beam spot is much larger than the lateral size of GQDs, the observed D-band appears to be dominated by edges of the GQDs rather than basal plane defects. In Fig. 4b, the FT-IR spectrum of the GQDs showed characteristic peaks corresponding to the CH band (2930 and 2850cm−1), CC band (1640cm−1), OH band (1386cm−1), and CO band (1120cm−1). In Fig. 4c, the XPS spectrum of the GQDs shows a dominant sp2 CC peak at 284.4eV and negligible oxygen functional groups such as CC (285.4eV), CO (286.2eV), CO (287.0eV), and OCOH (288.2eV) bonds.
